## 🧠 How It Works

```
Camera / Image
     │
     ▼
Offscreen <canvas> (sampled at col × row resolution)
     │
     ├─ getImageData() → pixel RGBA array
     │
     ├─ Per pixel:
     │    luminance → char index → character
     │    RGB → color function → fill color
     │
     ├─ ctx.fillText() per character onto visible canvas
     │
     └─ FX overlays: rain, scanlines, glitch, edge detection
```

1. Video/image is drawn into a small offscreen canvas at target resolution
2. `getImageData()` reads each pixel's RGBA values
3. Luminance maps to a character in the selected set (brighter = less dense)
4. The selected color mode determines each character's color
5. Characters are drawn with `ctx.fillText()` onto the visible canvas
6. Effect overlays (rain, glitch, scanlines, edges) are applied on top
7. Loop runs via `requestAnimationFrame` throttled to the chosen FPS cap

